A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Part 5 of Article 6 of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia
2 Annotated, relating to program weights and funding requirements under the "Quality Basic
3 Education Act," so as to provide for grants by the State Board of Education to local units of
4 administration to support students living in poverty; to provide for definitions; to require the
5 State Board of Education to develop rules and regulations; to provide for the calculation of
6 grant amounts; to provide that a minimum required portion of grant funds must be used by
7 local units of administration for direct program expenditures for the benefit of the students
8 living in poverty; to provide a short title; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting
9 laws; and for other purposes.
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
11 SECTION 1.
12 This Act shall be known and may be cited as the "Investing in Every Student Act."
13 SECTION 2.
14 Part 5 of Article 6 of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
15 relating to program weights and funding requirements under the "Quality Basic Education
