18 "20-2-189.
19 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
20 (1) 'Foster care student' means a student enrolled in a public school in this state who is
21 placed in a foster family home, child care institution, or another substitute care setting
22 approved by the Department of Human Services.
23 (2) 'Homeless student' means a student enrolled in a public school in this state who meets
24 the definition of the term 'homeless children and youths' under the federal
25 McKinney-Vento Homeless Assistance Act, codified at 42 U.S.C. Section 11301, et seq.,
26 in force and effect on January 1, 2025.
27 (3) 'Migrant student' means 'migrant student' means a child who is a student enrolled in
28 a public school in this state and who has, within 12 months prior to first becoming a
29 student in such school, moved across state, or school district system, or school attendance
30 zone lines with a migrant parent or guardian to enable the child, the child's parent or
31 guardian, or a member of the child's immediate family to obtain temporary or seasonal
32 employment in an agricultural or fishing activity.
33 (4) 'Student living in poverty' means a student enrolled in a public school in this state
34 who meets one or more of the following criteria:
35 (A) Lives in a family unit directly certified to be receiving Supplemental Nutrition
36 Assistance Program (SNAP) benefits;
37 (B) Lives in a family unit directly certified to be receiving Temporary Assistance for
38 Needy Families (TANF) benefits;
39 (C) Is a homeless student;
40 (D) Is a foster care student; or
41 (E) Is a migrant student.
